  "npcs": [
    {
      "id": "first-keeper",
      "name": "The First Keeper",
      "lines": [
        "Ten of us lit the First Anchor. Nine seats went cold. I am the count that remains, and I never stopped counting.",
        "Genesis was the first finality — the first promise that stayed promised. Everything you have anchored since is its interest.",
        "Forge the Seal at my brazier in the heart of the ring. A proof fragment and twenty shards — the hollow answers the Seal and nothing else.",
        "Seven founding seats ring the forge. Light them in the order they were born — wave, vertex, seal, anchor — once, and only once. A wrong seat snuffs them all.",
        "When the ring burns true, the nest-gate to the eye opens. Take my shards. I always knew someone would come — counting tells you that."
      ],
      "gift": {
        "shards": 12
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "cassio-bell",
      "name": "Cassio 'Quorum' Bell",
      "lines": [
        "Cassio Bell. Yes — that Cassio. Word reached the Settlement that Genesis runs seven-in-ten, and I rode three nightwaves to get here.",
        "The nest spits casters from every edge at once. Count your barricades before the count starts — arithmetic first, heroics never.",
        "Acolytes mend the pack from the seats; the vault-wraiths arc two-for-one across the pools. Burn the shielders early.",
        "The phaseborn walk straight through marble — your wall is a suggestion to them. Put bodies, not stone, between you and the seats.",
        "Here — my whole purse. If the First Anchor settles, money is only the second-best thing it buys back."
      ],
      "gift": {
        "shards": 7
      }
    }
  ],
